AI Safety and Policy

Google DeepMind on AGI: Google DeepMind emphasized the importance of preparing for Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). In a 145-page paper, they highlighted significant risks AGI might pose and proposed measures for mitigation through developer interventions, societal changes, and policy reforms. ​
Axios

Global AI Trends

Increased AI Adoption: A McKinsey survey indicated that 78% of organizations are using AI in at least one business function, up from 72% in early 2024. The use of generative AI has also seen a significant jump, with 71% of respondents reporting regular use in at least one business function. ​
McKinsey & Company

Focus on AI Optimization: Companies are shifting focus from merely implementing AI to optimizing its performance and maximizing value. More than 70% of organizations are already seeing returns on investment from generative AI, a number expected to rise as more companies move from production to optimization
